headline: Is Instacart Falling Behind As Amazon, Uber, And Walmart Battle For Grocery Customers?
summary: Maplebear Inc. (NASDAQ:CART), operating as Instacart, saw its shares decline on Friday after research highlighted topline risks associated with rising competition in online grocery delivery. headline: Instacart downgraded as competition tightening grip on online grocery
summary: Investing.com -- Piper Sandler cut its rating on Instacart to Neutral from Overweight, saying recent moves by Amazon, Walmart, Uber and DoorDash have intensified competitive pressure and left Instacart vulnerable to losing share."We move to the sidelines on CART in light of competitive pressures over the last month," Piper Sandler analysts said.

headline: Is DoorDash Partnership Expanding Yelp’s Role in Local Commerce and Shaping Its Investment Case (YELP)?
summary: DoorDash and Yelp recently announced a partnership, enabling Yelp users to access takeout and delivery from over 500,000 merchants nationwide through DoorDash’s delivery network. This collaboration combines Yelp’s trusted content with DoorDash’s technology, potentially expanding Yelp’s role as a central hub for local commerce and enhancing its core consumer offering. headline: DoorDash Canada Debuts BRING IT IN, Boldly Unifying Women’s Sports Sponsorships
summary: TORONTO, October 03, 2025--DoorDash Canada is now the official on-demand delivery platform partner of the Professional Women’s Hockey League (PWHL), joining its long-standing collaboration with the Women’s National Basketball Association (WNBA) and its founding partnership with the Northern Super League (NSL). The three trailblazing institutions anchor BRING IT IN: DoorDash Canada's boldest commitment yet to elevating women’s sports in Canada on a national stage.

headline: Why Maplebear (CART) Is Down 7.3% After Kroger Expands DoorDash Partnership and Analysts React
summary: In late September 2025, Instacart parent Maplebear Inc. faced intensified competition after Kroger, its third-largest customer, expanded its delivery partnership with DoorDash, prompting analysts to raise concerns about Instacart’s ability to retain key retail partners. This shift highlights the growing risk of major grocers diversifying their delivery partnerships, potentially increasing pressure on Instacart’s future revenue streams and business model stability.
